      "date": "2014-05-07 22:14:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n>I would prefer that we fix the test first and now. I think that what Andreas is suggesting is a performance improvement.\n\nIf we do things like andreas way, client will also do early lock cancel for data lock,  we do not need change test script at all. Actually both 120e and 120f intend to test OST lock ELC as well, you can see it caches OST locks on purpose after it clear client cache lock 1st time,\n\n        dd if=/dev/zero of=$DIR/$tdir/d1/f1 count=1\n        dd if=/dev/zero of=$DIR/$tdir/d2/f2 count=1\n        cancel_lru_locks mdc\n        cancel_lru_locks osc\n        dd if=$DIR/$tdir/d1/f1 of=/dev/null\n        dd if=$DIR/$tdir/d2/f2 of=/dev/null\n        stat $DIR/$tdir/d1 $DIR/$tdir/d2 $DIR/$tdir/d1/f1 $DIR/$tdir/d2/f2 > /dev/null",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
